bio: If there’s one thing Marcel cares about, it’s that you have fun during his classes and harness your inner power. The former soccer player has learned that giving back, supporting others and being present in the moment is much more powerful than any victory. In his classes, you can expect lots of motivation and positive vibes, as well as Marcel’s contagious smile.
short_bio: Marcel wants you to have fun during your workout. The former soccer player firmly believes that giving back, supporting others and being present in the moment is much more powerful than any victory. Celebrate every workout with him.
background: Soccer has been my passion ever since I can remember. I’ve taken all that fun, that spirit and the experiences of the game with me on my journey.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want to help you find your inner power. But most importantly, I want you to have fun. Let’s celebrate every workout together!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I try to be present in every moment, and instead of my successes, I celebrate my experiences—walks with my girlfriend and our dog Hugo, travels or football games. My vice is ice cream. I have at least one every day.'], ['', '']]
name: Marcel Maurer

bio: Hailing from Tampico, Mexico, Mariana grew up in a family full of athletes who drew on each other’s hard work and discipline to succeed. But as she grew older, her passion for teaching became evident as she loved helping others find their inner strength. A yoga teacher for over 11 years, Mariana has taught bilingual classes from Mexico City to NYC. Her classes are a mix of warmth, tough love and infectious energy. Her goal is to make you both smile and sweat.
short_bio: Hailing from Tampico, Mexico, Mariana will draw you to her empowering light with Spanish and English classes. With a competitive athletic background, movement, breath, energy and compassion are a huge part of Mariana’s practice.
background: I love when someone who is maybe a bit resistant to yoga takes class and feels they got as much of a workout as they did during a run, Bike ride, floor class.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I try to approach with an open heart, open mind and shining heart.'], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'Outside of Peloton, you can catch Mariana waiting in line to see the latest play or running and reading in Central Park. '], ['', '']]
name: Mariana Fernández

bio: Matty is always eager to bring his passion for fitness and his high-energy, entertaining teaching style to the Peloton community. A born entertainer, former television reporter and pop culture guru, Matty loves to infuse storytelling and humor into every workout. Everyone should feel at-home with Matty because when you're working out with him, you're part of the family.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I make it a party! I don’t believe that we need to suffer through our workouts. While it may not always be easy or comfortable, you’re going to be addicted to the way you feel after you’ve taken a class with me.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I watch entirely too much TV for a person who chose fitness as a career, but I promise, I’m a fitness freak! I’m also a wanderluster, theater queen, and “house head.” Odds are good I’ll probably retire on a bulldog farm.'], ['', '']]
quote: "You are not enough. You are everything!"
name: Matty Maggiacomo

bio: A former Division I distance runner with 10 years of coaching experience, Matt brings an encouraging energy grounded in athleticism to his teaching style. An avid cyclist, runner and traveler, Matt inspires Members to discover how strong they really are, and how fun training can be.
short_bio: "Train hard, train smart, and have fun!"
music_bio: Check out a sample of Matt’s current class playlist.
background: My passion is to help people. Nothing gets me more excited than helping my athletes achieve the results that they’ve dreamed of.
ordered_q_and_as:
[['How Do You Motivate?
', 'My goal is to make performance training fun! Members should come to class ready to work, and also have a good time doing it. 
'], ['Outside of Peloton
', 'Believe it or not, more fitness! Cycling, running and lifting are my favorites. I also enjoy traveling, and reading about fitness and business.
'], ['', '']]
quote: Train hard, train smart, and have fun!
name: Matt Wilpers

bio: After school, Mayla worked in Bali as a surf, fitness and yoga instructor. It was here she made her mark on the surf scene, before mentoring and motivating young women to find the confidence to make their way in the male-dominated world of surfing. Mayla now takes this spirit into her training. She loves helping people recognise their strengths and find the inner peace that comes from being comfortable in your own skin. Mayla’s personal experiences when added to her passion for fitness make her classes not only a great place to work up a sweat, but also a space to nourish the very things that make us human. Mayla works in our London studio and teaches classes in German.
short_bio: Mayla’s personal experiences in surfing and travelling when added to her natural passion for all-things fitness make her classes not only a great place to work up a sweat, but also a space to nourish the very things that make us human.
background: Every person is unique and that's what I want to celebrate in my classes. There is so much potential in each of us and my goal is to find all these treasures and bring them to the surface.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I have a strong connection to nature and the sea and I like to find parallels between the ocean and our lives. I want to inspire our members to look beyond their own horizons and discover other sides of life.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I love water! I grew up in a small town in the north of Germany surrounded by water. I've spent half my life in the water, but only surfing has captured my heart. So as often as I can, I go surfing."], ['', '']]
quote: Every moment is yours to be enjoyed.
name: Mayla Wedekind

bio: As an experienced fitness instructor, Mila wants you to have fun in her workouts and always follow your dreams. The professional dancer has traveled the world to live her personal dream. Now, she wants to share her experiences with you and motivate and support you. With lots of positive energy and passion, she will bring out the best in you and dance with you through every workout.
short_bio: Mila wants to inspire people to follow their dreams in her workouts. As a professional dancer and trainer, she has gained experience that she wants to pass on—with lots of fun, positive energy and passion.
background: I’m so proud that I keep on living my dream as a Peloton instructor. I’ve worked hard for years for this, but it was more than worth it to be here with you today.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "With passion and positive energy, I want to inspire others to discover themselves, live their dreams and give everything for them. It's so worth it. Even just for that feeling of happiness after every workout."], ['Outside of Peloton', "Whenever I have time, I dance. It doesn't matter if it's to hip hop or to house. I just love music and, more recently, podcasts and audiobooks too. I love diving into different worlds for hours on end."], ['', '']]
name: Mila Lazar

bio:
Nico is as versatile as her classes. The yoga trainer and meditation coach has already lived in New York, London, Berlin and Bali and has been inspired by a wide variety of cultures, teachings and yogis. Originally, she practiced yoga as a balance to her days at university in NYC but she soon discovered that yoga is much more than just a workout. Trained as a yoga teacher in Bali, Fiji, and Amsterdam, she developed her own flow which is characterized by positivity, motivation and fun. As a Peloton instructor, Nico wants you to get the best out of your training - physically and mentally.
Nico teaches her classes in German - produced in our Peloton studio in New York.
short_bio: Nico is not only a yoga trainer, but also a life coach. She enjoys incorporating this rich and varied knowledge into all her classes to give you a toolkit that will help you get the best out of you and your training.
background: Yoga is so much more than just a work-out. It's your work-in that will help you discover new ways to get more out of your workout.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate?', 'Whether you want to get fitter or more balanced - I want to give you a toolkit with yoga to master your everyday life even better. And with the right poses and the right attitude, you can achieve just about anything.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "My life is all about inspiration. Whether it's yoga, studying in New York, at home in Berlin or on holiday in Bali - open your eyes and your heart and the world will open up to you. "], ['', '']]
quote: Yoga is not just a work-out. It’s your work-in.
name: Nico Sarani

bio: Born and raised in New York, Olivia grew up playing and excelling at team sports, including lacrosse, field hockey, cheerleading and track. With a professional background in finance, as well as boxing and cycling, she brings a we-first, cheerleader approach to every class, inspiring you to leave each workout walking taller and feeling stronger.
short_bio: “Decide what you want to accomplish, and I will help you conquer it.”
background: We’re gonna work, and we’re gonna work hard. Know that I’m in this with you every step of the way. I’m a natural cheerleader, and when we workout together, we’re a team. I will always have your back, no matter how challenging things get!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I like to lead by example. By staying with you throughout class, I can show you that sometimes, all it takes is getting out of your own way to accomplish your goals. You’re going to love the way you feel when we’re done!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My first word was doggy, so you can imagine what my favorite animal is! I also love fashion, family, skincare, being outdoors, and being a crazy plant lady. '], ['', '']]
quote: “Decide what you want to accomplish, and I will help you conquer it.”
name: Olivia Amato

bio:
Rad was born and raised in the Bronx, NY in a vibrant Dominican household. Soft-spoken but resilient, he found his confidence through sports and competition. Years of hard work as a boxer led him into fitness and training. 

Physical and mental strength are key in Rad’s classes, and he’ll lead you through each workout with a little tough love. His goal is to inspire others to make them feel more confident about themselves.
background: It's a beautiful thing to be able to inspire others in a way that's going to make them feel more confident about themselves. To help someone better themselves both physically and mentally is a blessing.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I help you build a bigger sense of confidence. I’ll push you to find that determination within yourself, and get rid of any excuses. I make sure we have fun too, with a few dance moves and a great playlist.'], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'I’m always trying to learn new things—whether a new instrument or how to make a new dish for dinner. I’m a huge fan of my city, so I like finding new places to eat. I’m big on spending time with friends and family too. '], ['', '']]
name: Rad Lopez

bio: Rebecca’s background in dance, gymnastics and track & field laid a foundation for movement and body awareness that she brings to every Tread class. As a former bootcamp instructor, a Nike master trainer and much more, Rebecca aims to make every workout the best part of the day by celebrating movement and empowering through positivity.
background: Celebrating movement is the most liberating and charitable thing we can do for ourselves. My goal is to create a moment in everyone’s day that excites them to get moving and enjoy the body they are living in.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Movement is power. I’m here to empower you to do your best, every day. Challenges are not roadblocks, they’re reminders that we are stronger and more capable than we imagined, so rise up!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love to cook and travel! Adventure is in my blood. I love diving into culture by meeting new people, trying local food, recreating recipes from afar, conquering my fears, catching sunsets, and climbing mountains.'], ['', '']]
name: Rebecca Kennedy

bio: Peloton’s VP of Fitness Programming, Robin believes that sweat transforms lives. Her journey to Peloton came after she literally ran herself out of a successful law career. Robin is passionate about guiding Members past their limitations and excuses with inspiring, authentic anecdotes. Author of the New York Times bestseller Shut Up and Run, Robin is a RRCA-certified running coach and ultramarathoner. Her life’s mission is to redefine and rethink possibility through movement.
music_bio: Ready to ride? Check out a sample of Robin's current class playlist.
background: A life lived in sweat is my mission. Every day, I work hard planting seeds for tomorrow’s greatness. The hustle in me honors the hustle in you.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'With a heavy dose of tough love because iron sharpens iron. The pride of hard work lasts longer than the discomfort. And no matter what, just keep showing up.'], ['Outside of Peloton', ' Always searching for the next best sweat, you can catch me adding up miles and increasing reps around New York City and beyond.'], ['', '']]
name: Robin Arzón

bio: Ross first discovered yoga after experiencing a sports-related injury over 20 years ago. At the time, he was barely flexible enough to touch his toes! He soon discovered the healing and transformative properties of yoga and decided to commit to the practice fully. Ross became a scholar of physical healing, diving deep into biomechanics and the inner workings of the human body. Ross has traveled to more than 30 countries to teach, and loves connecting people with diverse backgrounds through yoga. In his classes, Ross invites Members to tap into their authentic selves through movement, exploring the strength of the human spirit along the way.
background: I love yoga because it allows me to experience the world through a uniquely philosophical lens. I love to learn and absorb the different ways to approach yoga and feel most fulfilled when serving or healing others.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'We’ve all been through challenging or painful experiences in life, but by turning inwards to explore our human spirit, we can recognize that we’re incredibly powerful beings and can accomplish anything we work towards.'], ['Outside of Peloton ', 'I love to travel, and for 30 years I’ve been a certified scuba diver. I’m also a big theater buff. So much so, that I married a theater director! I’m always surrounded by incredibly talented singers and dancers.'], ['', '']]
quote: The human spirit is stronger than we know. Trust it.
name: Ross Rayburn

bio: Sam is a pro at many things but shines when it comes to motivating Members to reach their best. From the ring to the dance floor, theatre to the music room, he’s spent his life studying his two passions: fitness and the arts. After 20 years in entertainment and 15 years in fitness, Sam is ready to challenge you to go further with a perfect balance of showmanship and hustle. Sam is based in the UK and teaches live rides from our London studio.
background: I’m a student of many different disciplines, as I know we all learn and absorb in different ways. Expect a mix of technical training, showmanship and a dash of serenity to help push you.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate?', 'I encourage Members to remember, “Why am I here?” That motivation is the element that gets us started, keeps us going and makes us want to come back for more. '], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I’m a huge film, theatre and comic buff! So you will definitely catch me at a musical, at the movies or on the couch catching up with a drama or comedy series. \r\n'], ['', '']]
name: Sam Yo

bio: Selena is a unique combination of an Italian upbringing and a Hawaiian state of mind. Raised in Italy in a family of professional soccer players, sports were a way of life. When she moved to Hawaii for college, she developed a passion for surfing and for the spiritual side of fitness. Relocating to NYC, she channeled this into a career training as an amateur boxer and teaching boxing. Selena brings an empowering energy to Peloton, teaching Members how to tap into themselves to unleash their power, and accomplish goals they never thought they could achieve.
background: I believe we’re all capable of great things and that we all have that fire burning inside us. I want to share the things that have helped me access that fire, and that’s exactly what I get to do on the Peloton Tread!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want Members to know that I’ve got their back, always. Every day we can push ourselves to new standards, get a little stronger, run a little faster, have a little more heart and show a little more power.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'Outside of Peloton you can find me on a surfboard or in boxing gloves. There is nothing quite like the feeling of being in perfect harmony with mother nature.'], ['', '']]
quote: DREAM IT. BELIEVE IT. RECEIVE IT.
name: Selena Samuela

bio:
When Susie’s brother convinced her to enter a half-marathon, it signalled a remarkable turning point for her. Previously more often found partying than PB-ing, Susie’s gone on to become one of the most recognisable faces in the British running community, a four-time Marathon des Sables finisher and a world record-breaker for treadmill running.
It’s no wonder she believes everyone can be a runner, setting you up for success by focussing on technique, comfort and ticking off achievable goals, regardless of your age or ability. This wickedly funny Brit is all about helping you be the best version of yourself today.
short_bio: Susie sets you up for success by focussing on your technique and comfort and helping you tick off achievable goals. Because she believes everyone can be a runner, this wickedly funny Brit helps you be the best version of yourself today.
background: I believe running is for everyone. From my own experience, I know that with a little bit of self-belief, combined with the magic of putting one foot in front of the other, anything is possible. I’m here to get you to where you want to be.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate? ', 'Being the best version of yourself on the day is all you can be. If you come to push yourself, to move or to have fun, I’ve got your back, and you’ll leave with a smile on your face.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My family, my dogs and travelling are my favourite things … and of course running! Spare time at home is spent exploring the trails with my friends. Downtime is spent reading, cooking and eating.'], ['', '']]
quote: DON'T BE DEFINED BY OTHER PEOPLE'S EXPECTATIONS. DEFINE YOUR OWN STRENGTHS.
name: Susie Chan

bio: Tobias is a sportsman through and through. When he's not coaching triathlons, he's preparing for the next ultra-marathon, skiing, playing football, tennis, basketball or giving his all in weight training. There is only one thing that is even more important to the native of Bamberg than sport: his two children and his wife, who share his love of running with him. If you want to train with an exceptional athlete, get the best out of yourself and also grow mentally, then Tobias’s running classes are just right for you.
short_bio: For Tobias, there are no limits to running and as a former aeronautical engineer, sport is above all science for him. He is all about getting the best out of himself and finishing every workout proud.
background: Limits only exist in the mind. And I want to show our members what they are capable of. That's exactly why I became a Peloton running instructor.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Running is connected to mental strength. I want to help others get the best out of themselves, and believing in yourself is the best motivation.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "My family is everything to me. Whether it's after an Iron Man or a normal workout, spending time with my two kids and my wife completely re-energises me."], ['', '']]
quote: Limits only exist in your mind. If you want, you can do so much more.
name: Tobias Heinze

bio: Tunde’s mission is to inspire and motivate other people to believe in the impossible. After years of struggling with her weight and self-confidence, Tunde fell in love with fitness and the doors it opened for her. Through a career as a celebrity makeup artist and brand educator, she discovered that she had a knack for teaching others to feel empowered and strong. Tunde brings an unparalleled positive energy to the Bike, fueled by personal experiences, perseverance and powerful playlists. There’s no doubt you’ll leave her classes feeling on top of the world.
short_bio: Tunde’s mission is to inspire and motivate other people to believe in the impossible. After overcoming challenging life experiences, Tunde radiates positivity and perseverance from the inside out.
background: I focus on crafting my classes with music that drives you. This rush of adrenaline allows you to move past the expectations or limitations you showed up with that day. Beyond that, I will always push you, but never let you fall.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "I motivate from experience. I'm on a forever journey, and have been in your shoes before. I will always push you, because I know you can come up from where you are, even if you haven’t fully realized it yet. "], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I’m from Texas, so Tex-Mex and margaritas have a special place in my heart. The beach is my happy place, laughing is my favorite thing to do and I’ll never turn down the chance to strut across a dance floor! '], ['', '']]
quote: Embrace the beauty of uncertainty. It’s a place of infinite possibility.
name: Tunde Oyeneyin

bio: Christian Vande Velde is a former American professional cyclist who most recently rode for Slipstream Sports/Team Garmin-Sharp. Christian's impressive palmarès from his time at Slipstream include: 2008 Team Time Trial victory at the Giro d’Italia, where he become only the second American ever to don the coveted maglia rosa; 2011 Tour de France Team Time Trial win and Best Team victory; two-time top 10 Overall Tour de France finisher (2008 and 2009); 2012 overall win at the USA Pro Cycling Challenge. Christian retired from racing in 2013 and is currently a commentator for NBC and NBCSN.
short_bio: Christian Vande Velde is a member of the Team Garmin-Sharp Professional Cycling Team.
name: Christian Vande Velde
